         <abstract>
            <p>Two difference approximations to the solution of a pseudo-parabolic problem are constructed and shown by means of stability analysis to converge in the "discrete" $L_2$ norm. A relation between parabolic and pseudo-parabolic difference schemes is discussed, and the stability of difference approximations to backward time parabolic and pseudo-parabolic problems is also considered.</p>
          </abstract>
